EXTRACTED VALUE: As a short, sharp blaze of fun, it's every bit as brash and ballsy as "Mercs" ever was. [July 2008, p.99]
Epic seizure-inducing madness that is the graphics. [Issue#37, p.117]
It's the most fun I've had flying online since "Crimson Skies" for the original Xbox. If only the single-player game flew as high.
MvA doesn’t do anything wrong per se, it’s just not the game that’s going to bring new fans over to the sport of motocross.
The fact that it is built upon completely ordinary tasks may seem pointless, but it's all the more believable for it.
